00:02:54.239 --> 00:02:59.680
sites are accessible
my goal with this talk is to help you

00:02:59.680 --> 00:03:03.599
recognize that implementing best
practices to make your website

00:03:03.599 --> 00:03:06.959
accessible will ensure a better user
experience for

00:03:06.959 --> 00:03:11.920
all of your site visitors i'll be
discussing various examples

00:03:11.920 --> 00:03:17.680
they are by no means exhaustive
and i hope that you will start thinking

00:03:17.680 --> 00:03:20.319
of your own examples as we go through
these

00:03:20.319 --> 00:03:26.000
and once everything is done
so there are a lot of reasons that

00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:29.440
people give about why
they won't make their sites accessible

00:03:29.440 --> 00:03:31.840
and i'm sure lots of you have heard a
lot of these

00:03:31.840 --> 00:03:38.080
already so the first one of course
it costs too much and there are a ton of

00:03:38.080 --> 00:03:41.680
counter arguments to this
but essentially the sooner you start

00:03:41.680 --> 00:03:45.200
recognizing and considering
accessibility the less it's going to

00:03:45.200 --> 00:03:50.239
cost
another one is it will wreck my design

00:03:50.239 --> 00:03:54.319
it might change your design but of
course you can still make beautiful

00:03:54.319 --> 00:04:00.319
creative and accessible websites
and the third one my site visitors don't

00:04:00.319 --> 00:04:03.439
have disabilities

00:04:04.080 --> 00:04:08.080
this is a giant fallacy which often goes
hand in hand

00:04:08.080 --> 00:04:12.239
with the misconception that
accessibility is purely for the sake

00:04:12.239 --> 00:04:17.919
of people with disabilities and for some
maybe to avoid lawsuits which is not the

00:04:17.919 --> 00:04:22.160
right reason
to be doing it not only do i guarantee

00:04:22.160 --> 00:04:25.440
though
that your site has visitors who have

00:04:25.440 --> 00:04:29.120
disabilities
i also know that an accessible website

00:04:29.120 --> 00:04:33.759
can have a positive impact on
anyone who visits that site we need to

00:04:33.759 --> 00:04:37.840
start understanding
that an accessible website is one that

00:04:37.840 --> 00:04:43.440
can easily be used
by everyone

00:04:43.440 --> 00:04:47.040
so you might be thinking how can i be so
sure

00:04:47.040 --> 00:04:51.040
that your site has visitors with
disabilities

00:04:51.040 --> 00:04:57.280
the answer is simple we have all
experienced disability some form of

00:04:57.280 --> 00:05:01.360
disability
in our lives and we will again

00:05:01.360 --> 00:05:06.560
often the image of a person with a
disability is somebody who is blind

00:05:06.560 --> 00:05:14.160
or deaf or has lost the use of a limb
these are considered permanent

00:05:14.160 --> 00:05:18.240
disabilities
but there are also temporary and

00:05:18.240 --> 00:05:24.639
situational disabilities
so to put these into context

00:05:24.639 --> 00:05:27.840
if you have an amputated arm that of
course

00:05:27.840 --> 00:05:31.520
would be a permanent disability but a
broken arm

00:05:31.520 --> 00:05:35.680
which would be a temporary disability
can have the same impact

00:05:35.680 --> 00:05:39.840
on how you function and an armful of
groceries

00:05:39.840 --> 00:05:44.000
also prevents you from using that arm
for other purposes

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:48.960
for a very short period of time that's
situational

00:05:48.960 --> 00:05:52.560
and there are lots of accessibility
considerations that make life

00:05:52.560 --> 00:05:57.840
easier for people who aren't
experiencing any form of disability

00:05:57.840 --> 00:06:00.960
so let's get to some examples and as i
said

00:06:00.960 --> 00:06:05.919
these are by no means exhaustive there
are a million different examples

00:06:05.919 --> 00:06:09.600
and we're not going to touch on every
type of

00:06:09.600 --> 00:06:17.199
disability but i hope these get you
to start thinking so first scenario

00:06:17.199 --> 00:06:20.479
you get home from work and you have to
feed your kids

00:06:20.479 --> 00:06:26.720
you have a migraine the kids are excited
and loud which adds to the brain fog

00:06:26.720 --> 00:06:30.080
from your migraine
you decide to order delivery from a

00:06:30.080 --> 00:06:32.639
website

00:06:32.800 --> 00:06:36.880
so let's discuss some of the potential
barriers that could make this

00:06:36.880 --> 00:06:42.160
a difficult experience for you in this
scenario

00:06:45.520 --> 00:06:50.560
confusing navigation hard to find
buttons and links

00:06:50.560 --> 00:06:53.599
these need to be clear where you're
going to click

00:06:53.599 --> 00:06:57.919
in order to get to the ordering portal
to add items to your cart

00:06:57.919 --> 00:07:01.120
to pay for your order all of these kinds
of things

00:07:01.120 --> 00:07:05.759
otherwise you'll end up getting confused
and frustrated

00:07:05.759 --> 00:07:09.919
too many calls to action fighting for
your attention

00:07:09.919 --> 00:07:14.080
when you can barely think because of the
migraine and brain fog that you have

00:07:14.080 --> 00:07:16.720
going on
these are distractions that are too hard

00:07:16.720 --> 00:07:21.199
to cope with
so again confusion can ensue

00:07:21.199 --> 00:07:25.599
fast-moving animations similar to too
many ctas

00:07:25.599 --> 00:07:30.319
but also these can make your headache
worse and make it hard for you to even

00:07:30.319 --> 00:07:37.120
look at the screen and finally
some checkout form issues input field

00:07:37.120 --> 00:07:40.560
labels used as placeholder text that
disappear

00:07:40.560 --> 00:07:44.000
when you start typing in that field i've
been caught by

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:47.919
these when i'm not giving my sight of my
full attention

00:07:47.919 --> 00:07:53.599
even without a headache imagine in our
scenario

00:07:53.599 --> 00:07:58.000
you click into a field you hear a crash
in the living room that distracts

00:07:58.000 --> 00:08:01.680
you and when you return back to that
form

00:08:01.680 --> 00:08:05.120
and return your attention there you have
no recollection

00:08:05.120 --> 00:08:09.919
of what that input field was for and
what you were supposed to enter there

00:08:09.919 --> 00:08:14.319
and something i see less often but
certainly has happened

00:08:14.319 --> 00:08:18.800
the inability to click into a field can
baffle in frustrate

00:08:18.800 --> 00:08:23.520
and make you think that it's impossible
to complete this order

00:08:23.599 --> 00:08:28.319
all of these factors could result in you
giving up on placing an order on this

00:08:28.319 --> 00:08:31.680
site
and taking your business elsewhere not

00:08:31.680 --> 00:08:36.320
to mention
adding to just the general frustration

00:08:36.320 --> 00:08:41.120
and chaos that's happening
around you migraines fall under the

00:08:41.120 --> 00:08:45.040
neurological category
which would include other things such as

00:08:45.040 --> 00:08:49.200
adhd
autism and epilepsy as permanent

00:08:49.200 --> 00:08:52.800
disabilities
so who else can benefit from

00:08:52.800 --> 00:08:56.320
neurological considerations

00:08:56.720 --> 00:09:01.440
i'm sure you can all relate to at least
one of these situations

00:09:01.440 --> 00:09:06.560
brain fog which can happen on its own or
can be a result of a lack of sleep

00:09:06.560 --> 00:09:12.959
or a flu or cold
mental health concerns like anxiety

00:09:12.959 --> 00:09:18.880
depression even general stress
can impact your ability to focus and

00:09:18.880 --> 00:09:22.560
process
what you see on a site as well as simply

00:09:22.560 --> 00:09:29.920
being in a distracting environment
neurological accessibility benefits

00:09:29.920 --> 00:09:32.560
everyone

00:09:33.040 --> 00:09:39.279
so our next scenario you decide to
remote work from a local coffee shop

00:09:39.279 --> 00:09:43.760
i used to do this all the time you get
stuck on a problem

00:09:43.760 --> 00:09:48.160
and search for a tutorial you find the
perfect video

00:09:48.160 --> 00:09:55.360
embedded on its own web page but darn it
you forgot your headphones at home

00:09:55.519 --> 00:09:59.040
so what are some potential complications
here

00:09:59.040 --> 00:10:03.440
first if there are no closed captions or
subtitling available

00:10:03.440 --> 00:10:07.839
you can't watch it on mute and know
what's being said

00:10:07.839 --> 00:10:11.440
if video is the only way the information
is presented

00:10:11.440 --> 00:10:16.399
there's no transcript or blog post that
sums up that information

00:10:16.399 --> 00:10:20.320
both of these result in you being unable
to get the information

00:10:20.320 --> 00:10:26.640
that you need when you need it
the last item isn't necessarily a

00:10:26.640 --> 00:10:29.440
barrier
but definitely has the potential to

00:10:29.440 --> 00:10:34.160
cause issues
and embarrassment the video is set

00:10:34.160 --> 00:10:37.200
to autoplay

00:10:37.360 --> 00:10:41.920
and as soon as the page loads the audio
is streaming out of your laptop for

00:10:41.920 --> 00:10:47.040
all to hear personally i've actually
been startled by autoplaying videos

00:10:47.040 --> 00:10:52.240
before
even on sites i repeatedly visit

00:10:52.240 --> 00:10:56.880
these issues are all audio related and
certainly affect people who have some

00:10:56.880 --> 00:11:00.720
form of permanent hearing loss
but there are a variety of other people

00:11:00.720 --> 00:11:05.839
who can benefit from text alternatives
to audio

00:11:05.839 --> 00:11:09.760
people with temporary hearing loss due
to tinnitus

00:11:09.760 --> 00:11:14.560
or a plugged ear that could be caused
from an ear infection or allergies

00:11:14.560 --> 00:11:19.680
or even if you've been traveling and
just got off a plane

00:11:19.680 --> 00:11:24.480
i often prefer to skim through text to
find a quick answer rather than watching

00:11:24.480 --> 00:11:29.120
a video
and some people simply process

00:11:29.120 --> 00:11:33.839
information better by reading it rather
than listening to it

00:11:33.839 --> 00:11:38.399
people learning a new language may use
subtitles to follow along

00:11:38.399 --> 00:11:42.959
and help them learn and understand the
language better

00:11:42.959 --> 00:11:46.000
and of course in this age we have
digital assistants

00:11:46.000 --> 00:11:51.279
like siri google assistant alexa and
they can all read text from websites

00:11:51.279 --> 00:11:55.360
if it's there and of course loud
environments in general

00:11:55.360 --> 00:11:58.560
can make it very hard to understand what
is being said

00:11:58.560 --> 00:12:05.839
in audio audio accessibility
benefits everyone

00:12:05.920 --> 00:12:11.360
so our third scenario
you're a wordpress developer who never

00:12:11.360 --> 00:12:16.800
takes their hands off the keyboard
you know all the keyboard shortcuts and

00:12:16.800 --> 00:12:20.160
there is
not a mouse to be found anywhere in your

00:12:20.160 --> 00:12:23.680
office
you decide to register in an online

00:12:23.680 --> 00:12:26.399
course
for the latest and greatest headless

00:12:26.399 --> 00:12:28.880
platform

00:12:29.360 --> 00:12:35.200
so let's look at some of the barriers
you might experience with this scenario

00:12:35.440 --> 00:12:39.200
no skip to content option which means
you have to tap through

00:12:39.200 --> 00:12:44.320
every single item in the header before
getting to the main part of the page

00:12:44.320 --> 00:12:48.399
add to that a main navigation that
forces you to tap through every sub

00:12:48.399 --> 00:12:54.240
item and you may feel like it's never
going to get off of the header

00:12:54.240 --> 00:12:58.000
no focus indication means you can't see
where you are

00:12:58.000 --> 00:13:01.120
on that page what link or button you
might click

00:13:01.120 --> 00:13:06.160
if you hit enter and we've got
unexpected tab behavior

00:13:06.160 --> 00:13:09.920
which can take you all over the page in
some random

00:13:09.920 --> 00:13:15.680
exp experiences and i've seen where it
goes straight from the skip to content

00:13:15.680 --> 00:13:18.480
right down to the bottom to the chat box
that they have

00:13:18.480 --> 00:13:22.959
then back up to the top and then into
the middle

00:13:24.240 --> 00:13:27.600
and that's just so confusing when you're
trying to

00:13:27.600 --> 00:13:32.320
follow the flow of the page
and then by the time you finally read

00:13:32.320 --> 00:13:36.800
the information about the course
and decide to register you may encounter

00:13:36.800 --> 00:13:39.839
keyboard chops
like not being able to return to a field

00:13:39.839 --> 00:13:42.720
once it's filled out
or not being able to leave the

00:13:42.720 --> 00:13:48.240
registration form unless you hit submit
these are frustrations that people with

00:13:48.240 --> 00:13:51.519
physical disabilities
who need to use keyboards or other

00:13:51.519 --> 00:13:57.600
special devices to navigate websites
face all the time so here are some other

00:13:57.600 --> 00:14:00.880
examples of when you might need or want
to rely solely

00:14:00.880 --> 00:14:03.839
on your keyboard

00:14:04.000 --> 00:14:07.680
you may have a broken arm a broken wrist
a broken finger

00:14:07.680 --> 00:14:13.920
anything on that limb that is
just not functioning or even even if it

00:14:13.920 --> 00:14:17.760
does function
i've had my finger broken before and you

00:14:17.760 --> 00:14:20.800
get that splint on it and try using a
mouse

00:14:20.800 --> 00:14:25.279
with a splint on your finger it just
doesn't work

00:14:25.519 --> 00:14:29.360
maybe you have carpal tunnel syndrome or
something else that flares up temp

00:14:29.360 --> 00:14:35.040
every now and then but not all the time
maybe you have a wireless mouse and the

00:14:35.040 --> 00:14:39.279
battery died and you don't have any
extra batteries in the house

00:14:39.279 --> 00:14:42.959
or my personal favorite you have a
sleeping baby or pet

00:14:42.959 --> 00:14:46.959
on your lap my dog loves to sit on my
lap

00:14:46.959 --> 00:14:50.000
and rest his head on my dominant arm and
i

00:14:50.000 --> 00:14:53.600
hate to disturb him so i don't move my
arm

00:14:53.600 --> 00:14:57.360
i just put it in position on the
keyboard i try to type

00:14:57.360 --> 00:15:01.600
as best i can and use my other hand as
well

00:15:01.600 --> 00:15:06.880
so keyboard accessibility benefits
everyone

00:15:08.079 --> 00:15:13.600
our last scenario you live in oregon
on the west coast in the united states

00:15:13.600 --> 00:15:17.920
and it's three weeks ago
temperatures are high and you don't have

00:15:17.920 --> 00:15:21.360
an air conditioner so windows need to be
open

00:15:21.360 --> 00:15:25.760
wildfires break out all around you
causing poor air quality

00:15:25.760 --> 00:15:29.600
that irritates your eyes and blurs your
vision

00:15:29.600 --> 00:15:34.399
you have to evacuate to a more rural
area that has poor wi-fi

00:15:34.399 --> 00:15:37.680
and you're going to work remotely while
you're there and you need to visit a

00:15:37.680 --> 00:15:44.639
variety of websites throughout the day
so let's look at our barriers here

00:15:44.639 --> 00:15:48.000
when you have blurry eyes trying to read
small

00:15:48.000 --> 00:15:54.560
or skinny font text is
really difficult low contrast between

00:15:54.560 --> 00:15:56.800
the
foreground and the background can make

00:15:56.800 --> 00:15:59.040
it hard to see information when you're
trying

00:15:59.040 --> 00:16:02.800
to get your eyes to focus and they won't
linked text

00:16:02.800 --> 00:16:06.160
can be hard to notice if it's only using
color

00:16:06.160 --> 00:16:10.959
to differentiate from regular text and
if the colors are too similar

00:16:10.959 --> 00:16:14.959
maybe you want to zoom in to make it
easier to read the content

00:16:14.959 --> 00:16:21.199
but the layout isn't suited to resizing
so images and maybe even text go off the

00:16:21.199 --> 00:16:25.680
side of the screen
and you can't access it and if images

00:16:25.680 --> 00:16:29.279
don't load because of
the weak wi-fi and there's no

00:16:29.279 --> 00:16:32.720
alternative text
you could be missing out on important

00:16:32.720 --> 00:16:37.360
information
these all fall into the visual category

00:16:37.360 --> 00:16:41.680
affecting people who have color
blindness or reduced vision

00:16:41.680 --> 00:16:45.360
and again we have lots of scenarios that
can affect your ability

00:16:45.360 --> 00:16:48.240
to see a website

00:16:48.480 --> 00:16:52.079
you may have an eye injury maybe you had
eye surgery or an

00:16:52.079 --> 00:16:58.000
eye infection i heard this mentioned in
another talk earlier you know

00:16:58.000 --> 00:17:01.680
there's a typo on this slide but the
dilated

00:17:01.680 --> 00:17:06.319
eyes from having an eye exam when you
get those drops in your eyes

00:17:06.319 --> 00:17:09.520
another form of migraine is an oral
migraine

00:17:09.520 --> 00:17:14.400
which can cause part or all of your
vision to be obscured

00:17:14.400 --> 00:17:18.160
bright sun either shining directly on
your eyes

00:17:18.160 --> 00:17:22.240
or on your screen can make it hard to
see when the contrast

00:17:22.240 --> 00:17:28.319
isn't very different allergies
similar to the smoke irritant in our

00:17:28.319 --> 00:17:32.640
scenario
can cause your eyes to blur

00:17:32.640 --> 00:17:37.600
or maybe something as simple as you
forgot your reading glasses

00:17:37.600 --> 00:17:42.720
visual accessibility benefits everyone

00:17:44.400 --> 00:17:48.640
all of these scenarios are real life
examples many that i have personally

00:17:48.640 --> 00:17:52.960
experienced
or know somebody who has maybe you can

00:17:52.960 --> 00:17:57.679
relate to one or two of them
maybe you can relate to a lot of them

00:17:57.679 --> 00:18:00.799
either way
i challenge you to come up with your own

00:18:00.799 --> 00:18:05.120
examples that you can share with others
that will help accessibility

00:18:05.120 --> 00:18:09.919
considerations become more
commonplace and at the very least

00:18:09.919 --> 00:18:14.400
i hope i have convinced you that making
your website accessible

00:18:14.400 --> 00:18:18.799
makes it better for everyone

00:18:19.039 --> 00:18:25.200
thank you for listening you can find me
on twitter send me an email and of

00:18:25.200 --> 00:18:28.720
course gratuitous plug for my podcast wp
contribute

00:18:28.720 --> 00:18:33.360
on all of the podcast players

